TONIGHT!! MCO Experimental Pop Showcase: Makeunder, Bill Baird, + Frontiers
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Mission Creek Oakland + Oaktown Indie Mayhem Co-present an experimental indie pop lineup of which dreams are made. Come on out and enjoy some sonic deliciousness from Makeunder, Bill Baird, + Frontiers. Makeunder An experimental pop band, Makeunder raises live music to a whole new level with their diy orchestral antics, a solid serving of Oakland style soul, and a dash of dirty rock n roll vibes to round it out. Featuring an all star cast, this is surely an en ensemble that shant disappoint. @[NjQyMTgzOTU5MjA4MTA3Omh0dHBzXGEvL3d3dy5mYWNlYm9vay5jb20vV2VBcmVNYWtldW5kZXI6Og==:https://www.facebook.com/WeAreMakeunder] Bill Baird In a post everything land where intentional repetition, the perfect amount of slapback, and 70's style psych rock vibes are the calling card of awesomeness, Bill Baird is here to deliver a dynamic set of epic proportions. Providing you, the spectator, with enough material to keep your mind turning for days, he'll also have no problem getting your body on the dance floor. No go get you some. @[NjQyMTgzOTU5MjA4MTA3Omh0dHBzXGEvL3d3dy5mYWNlYm9vay5jb20vYmxvbmRlYmlsbDo6:https://www.facebook.com/blondebill] Frontiers Atmospheric post-rock to set the mood, Oakland's very own Frontiers will send chills up your spine with their ethereal sound. Looking for a little experimental progressive indie rock to sidle up to some fine looking stranger? Why yes, its just what you asked for indeed. @[NjQyMTgzOTU5MjA4MTA3Omh0dHBzXGEvL3d3dy5mYWNlYm9vay5jb20vcGFnZXMvRnJvbnRpZXJzLzI4MjU2ODI5ODU3NzcyODo6:https://www.facebook.com/pages/Frontiers/282568298577728] Sat 9/6/14 Doors at 8pm Show at 9pm $7 - MCO Edition

OneBeat SF - Presented by Found Sound Nation and The Global Lives Project
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Wednesday, October 15 // 7pm // Public Works // Free 7-8pm Doors open 8-10pm Live performances 10pm+ DJ sets Public Works 161 Erie Street (off Mission between Duboce & 14th) San Francisco, CA 94103 **Cash bar** Bang on a Can's Found Sound Nation and the Global Lives Project, in partnership with Compound, present OneBeatSF, a music-media event featuring 20+ artists and musicians mixing melodies, vocals and beats against the backdrop of Global Lives: Transit—video installations on the perpetual motion of our world, from Colombia to Kazakhstan, Indonesia, Malawi and more. A one-of-a-kind audio-video jam, performances at OneBeatSF are a radical re-imagining of 'world music' - with works created exclusively for this event via a seven-day collaboration-convergence of artists and musicians from around the globe. Colombian percussion, Arabic classical vocals, Ukrainian indie rock, reimagined Kyrgyz folk tunes and more, will be juxtaposed against videos of everyday life from around the world produced by the Global Lives Collective. OneBeatSF's main performance will take place at Public Works in San Francisco on Wednesday, October 15th and is preceded by roving OneBeatSF ensemble performances and video-shoots earlier in the day throughout the city, in collaboration with the creative agency, Projector. All performances are free and open to the public--details on locations of roving performances will be listed soon! OneBeatSF is sponsored by OneBeat, the touring music residency initiative of the U.S. Department of State’s Bureau of Cultural and Educational Affairs, and is produced by Bang on a Can's Found Sound Nation with Compound, and presented with The Global Lives Project’s "Global Wednesdays" event series. **Read about OneBeat in the SF Weekly!** World Music Reimagined at OneBeat SF http://www.sfweekly.com/shookdown/2014/10/07/world-music-re-imagined-at-onebeat-sf
Wednesday, October 15, 2014, 7 PM - 11 PM in PDT

What's the WERD? | w/ MARK SLEE (House-Heads | Manju Masi)
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
This week's installment of your friendly neighborhood techno soiree features a very talented local DJ making his first appearance, MARK SLEE. We have had this man on the short list for a number of months and every time we see him, he leaves us nothing short of impressed! Come catch his eclectic, deep, technical sound this Sunday! His Soundcloud (https://soundcloud.com/mcslee) is chock full! .. go on.... have a listen! NO COVER before 11PM BLUE ANGEL vodka drink specials all night long! ______________________________ MARK SLEE Mark Slee is a resident DJ and co-founder of House-Heads, a San Francisco collective throwing unique underground and private events focused on forward-thinking dance music. He is also one half of Manju Masi, a collaboration with long-time partner in crime Atish. Born and raised outside Chicago, Mark grew up on a steady diet of electronic music. Early influences came from eclectic acts like Orbital, Aphex Twin, and Underworld, balanced against an exposure to the more dancefloor-oriented sounds of Chicago house. A student of the piano from a young age, he quickly developed a keen interest in audio production and DJing - an interest he has now cultivated for 15 years. Living in San Francisco since 2005, Mark has evolved a style of DJing that uniquely reflects his personality. Technical and introspective, he brings a thoughtful approach to constructing sets that tickle both mind and soul, at the same time topping things off with a healthy dose of groovy, quirky fun. Understanding audio to be one avenue of a larger experience, 2011 has seen him return to original production, crafting custom-tailored tracks for the unique events he produces with House-Heads, often complementing them with interactive LED sculptures that he also creates.
Sunday, December 16, 2012 at 9:00pm - Monday, December 17, 2012 at 2:00am in PST
